Clean up of logs for system to run smoothly
On the basis of  number of days logs can be deleted
find and -m
find . filename - for pwd
find 'path' filename - for a particular path
mtime - last time content was edited in the file - it is thelatest time 
-mtime +30 retrieve files > 30 days
-mtime - 30 is <30days
creating a file that looks like a old file with old date:
touch -a -m -t 201412151230.05 f1.txt a = accesse time, -m = modified time t = timestamp
for deleting old files in /root/
#!/bin/bash
echo "deletes old file"
path=$1
echo $path
find $path -mtime +30 -delete
if [ $? -eq 0 ]
then
echo "files old deleted"
else
        "deletion has issues"
fi

run as ./script.sh /root/
[root@ip-172-31-38-159 ~]# ./deletingold.sh /root/
deletes old file
/root/
files old deleted
